        FLASH LEARNING — HOW THE WEBSITE WORKS
================================================================


----------------------------------------------------------------
 WHAT IS FLASH LEARNING?
----------------------------------------------------------------

Flash Learning is an online peer-to-peer tutoring platform built
for university and high school students in Cameroon. It connects
students who need academic help with qualified tutors who can
teach them — either online or in person on campus. Payments are
made via Mobile Money (MTN MoMo or Orange Money).


----------------------------------------------------------------
 THE THREE USER ROLES
----------------------------------------------------------------

  STUDENT
    A student signs up, sets up their profile, browses tutors,
    books sessions, accesses study materials, and chats with
    tutors. They pay for sessions through Mobile Money.

  TUTOR
    A tutor signs up, fills in their profile (qualification,
    subjects, bio, photo), and waits for admin approval. Once
    approved, students can see them, book sessions with them,
    and message them. Tutors can also upload study materials
    (PDFs) for students to access.

  ADMIN
    The admin is a single hardcoded account:
      Email    : admin@flashlearn.edu
      Password : Admin@FL2024
    The admin approves tutors, manages all users, monitors
    sessions, views platform revenue, and can delete messages
    or materials.


----------------------------------------------------------------
 HOW A STUDENT USES THE SITE
----------------------------------------------------------------

  1.  Goes to index.html (splash page) and clicks Sign Up
  2.  Fills in name, email, password, selects "Student" role
  3.  Gets redirected to dashboard-student.html
  4.  Sets up their profile — date of birth, optional photo,
      and subjects they need help with
  5.  The overview page shows recommended tutors based on
      those subjects
  6.  To book a session:
        - Clicks "Book Session" in the sidebar
        - Searches for a tutor by name or subject
        - Selects a tutor
        - Fills in subject, date, time, and mode
          (online or onsite)
        - Chooses payment method (MTN MoMo or Orange Money)
        - Enters their phone number
        - Payment is processed → booking is confirmed
  7.  The booked session appears in "My Sessions" with status
      "pending" until the tutor confirms it
  8.  Students can access study notes and past papers in the
      "Study Notes" and "Q&A Bank" sections
  9.  Students can message any tutor directly through the
      "Messages" section


----------------------------------------------------------------
 HOW A TUTOR USES THE SITE
----------------------------------------------------------------

  1.  Goes to index.html → clicks Sign Up → selects "Tutor"
  2.  Gets redirected to dashboard-tutor.html
  3.  A basic profile is auto-created immediately so they
      appear in the system right away
  4.  They fill in their full profile:
        - Date of birth
        - Qualification (Certificate / Diploma / Bachelor /
          Master / PhD)
        - Subjects they teach
        - Bio and optional photo
  5.  Hourly rate is set automatically by qualification:

        Certificate  →  3,000 XAF/hr
        Diploma      →  4,000 XAF/hr
        Bachelor     →  5,000 XAF/hr
        Master       →  7,000 XAF/hr
        PhD          → 10,000 XAF/hr

  6.  Admin must approve their profile before students can
      book them (students can still message them immediately)
  7.  When a student books a session, it appears in the
      tutor's "My Schedule" with status "pending"
  8.  The tutor can update the session status to:
        confirmed / completed / cancelled
  9.  Tutors can upload PDF study materials (notes, past
      papers, exercises) for students to access
  10. Tutors can view their earnings in "My Earnings":
        - Gross amount paid by student
        - 15% platform fee deducted
        - Their 85% net earnings per session


----------------------------------------------------------------
 HOW THE ADMIN USES THE SITE
----------------------------------------------------------------

  1.  Logs in at login.html with the hardcoded credentials
  2.  Gets redirected to dashboard-admin.html

  Dashboard sections:

    Overview    — Live counts: students, tutors, sessions
                  this month, messages, pending sessions,
                  and pending tutor approvals

    Users       — All registered users, filter by role,
                  remove any user

    Tutors      — All tutor profiles, approve or revoke
                  approval, manually set hourly rate

    Sessions    — Every session on the platform, update
                  any session's status

    Materials   — All uploaded study materials, delete any

    Chat        — Monitor all messages, delete any message

    Revenue     — Total gross revenue, platform's 15% cut,
                  total tutor payouts, breakdown per tutor

    Settings    — Platform name, support email, phone,
                  min/max session rates, maintenance mode


----------------------------------------------------------------
 THE PAYMENT SYSTEM
----------------------------------------------------------------

  When a student books a session and pays (e.g. 5,000 XAF):

    Full amount paid by student  →  5,000 XAF
    Platform fee (15%)           →    750 XAF  (to admin)
    Tutor receives (85%)         →  4,250 XAF

  - The split is calculated and stored in the database at
    the moment of booking
  - Tutors see their net earnings in their dashboard
  - The admin sees total platform revenue in the Revenue
    section
  - Full details are in the Terms of Use page (terms.html)


