 GOOGLE MAPS — HOW IT WAS IMPLEMENTED
----------------------------------------------------------------

  The map appears on the Contact page (contact.html) under
  the heading "Locate our Tutoring Hub". It shows the location
  of the tutoring hub so students can find their scheduled
  onsite meeting spot.


  HOW IT WORKS
  -------------
  No Google Maps API key was used. The map was embedded using
  Google Maps' free Embed URL feature, which generates a
  shareable iframe link directly from Google Maps. This
  requires no account, no billing, and no JavaScript SDK.


  STEP 1 — Get the embed URL from Google Maps
  --------------------------------------------
  1. Go to maps.google.com
  2. Search for the location you want to show
  3. Click Share → Embed a map
  4. Google generates a full <iframe> code with a src URL
     in this format:
       https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!...
  5. Copy that URL


  STEP 2 — Place it inside a responsive container
  ------------------------------------------------
  Bootstrap's ratio utility class was used to make the map
  responsive. The class "ratio ratio-21x9" forces the iframe
  to maintain a 21:9 widescreen aspect ratio on all screen
  sizes without needing fixed pixel heights.

  The full HTML used:

    <div class="ratio ratio-21x9 rounded-4 shadow overflow-hidden border">
        <iframe
            src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=..."
            allowfullscreen=""
            loading="lazy">
        </iframe>
    </div>

  Breakdown of each attribute:

    ratio ratio-21x9     — Bootstrap class that makes the
                           iframe scale responsively at a
                           21:9 aspect ratio

    rounded-4            — Bootstrap class for rounded corners

    shadow               — Bootstrap class for a drop shadow

    overflow-hidden      — clips the map corners so they
                           respect the border-radius

    border               — adds a subtle border around the map

    allowfullscreen=""   — lets the user expand the map to
                           full screen if they want

    loading="lazy"       — the map only loads when the user
                           scrolls near it, improving page
                           load speed


  STEP 3 — Caption below the map
  --------------------------------
  A small instruction line was added below the map:

    "Use the map to find your scheduled onsite meeting spot."

  This tells students why the map is there — to help them
  locate the physical location for onsite sessions.


  WHERE IT APPEARS
  -----------------
  - contact.html  (the Contact page, in the lower section
                   below the contact form and details)


  IMPORTANT NOTE
  ---------------
  The current embed URL points to a placeholder location
  (Envato in Melbourne, Australia) because the real campus
  location was not provided during development. To update it
  to the correct location:

    1. Go to maps.google.com
    2. Search for the actual tutoring hub address
    3. Click Share → Embed a map → Copy the iframe src URL
    4. Replace the src value in contact.html with the new URL


