----------------------------------------------------------------
 GOOGLE MAPS — HOW IT WAS IMPLEMENTED
----------------------------------------------------------------

  The map is embedded on the Contact page (contact.html) and
  shows the location of the Catholic University of Cameroon,
  which is the physical tutoring hub for onsite sessions.


  HOW IT WORKS
  -------------
  Google Maps was embedded using a free Google Maps Embed URL.
  No API key is required for this method. The map is loaded
  inside an HTML <iframe> element directly on the page.

  The embed URL format used:
    https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=[encoded location data]

  The place identifier used to pin the exact location:
    Place  : Catholic University of Cameroon
    Place ID: 0x0:0x2366174a3388a463
    Source : https://www.google.com/maps/place/
             Catholic+University+of+Cameroon


  THE HTML CODE USED
  -------------------
  A Bootstrap responsive ratio wrapper (ratio-21x9) is used
  so the map scales correctly on all screen sizes:

    <div class="ratio ratio-21x9 rounded-4 shadow
                overflow-hidden border">
        <iframe
            src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=..."
            allowfullscreen=""
            loading="lazy"
            referrerpolicy="no-referrer-when-downgrade">
        </iframe>
    </div>

  Key attributes explained:

    ratio ratio-21x9    — Bootstrap class that makes the
                          iframe maintain a 21:9 aspect ratio
                          and fill its container responsively

    allowfullscreen     — lets the user expand the map to
                          full screen inside the browser

    loading="lazy"      — the map only loads when the user
                          scrolls to it, improving page speed

    referrerpolicy      — controls what information is sent
    no-referrer-when    — to Google when the map loads
    -downgrade


  WHERE IT APPEARS
  -----------------
  - contact.html — under the heading "Locate our Tutoring Hub"
  - A note below the map reads: "Use the map to find your
    scheduled onsite meeting spot."


  WHY NO API KEY?
  ----------------
  Google Maps offers a free embed option that does not require
  an API key. You simply use the /maps/embed URL with the
  place data encoded in the URL. This is suitable for simple
  location display. An API key would only be needed if you
  wanted interactive features like directions, custom markers,
  or Street View integration.


